OL,3,CHare who survived caesarean birth is
OL,4,Cnow 'growing stronger every day'
OL,6,FA baby hare who survived a caesarean
OL,7,Fbirth after his mother died in a
OL,8,Ffarming accident is now 'growing
OL,9,Fstronger every day' under the care of
OL,10,Fthe Scottish SPCA.
OL,12,FSeven-week-old Bruno, dubbed 'Bruno
OL,13,Fthe Brave', was saved by Dumfriesshire
OL,14,Ffarmer Robert Craig while he was
OL,15,Fharvesting, in which Bruno's mother
OL,16,Fwas accidentally killed on 13 May 2025.
OL,18,FMr. Craig says he noticed movement
OL,19,Fafter checking the animal's belly. He
OL,20,Fsaid: "I went to check what I had
OL,21,Fstruck and sadly found the hare dead.
OL,26,@|D@GOU
