OL,6,FAnimal Rescue Officer Emma Totney, who
OL,7,Fattended the scene, said: "When I
OL,8,Farrived, I was surprised by how alert
OL,9,Fand energetic the baby was ` it was a
OL,10,Fhuge relief. He was feeding well and
OL,11,Falready showing signs of real fight."
OL,13,FBruno was provided 24/7 care at the
OL,14,FFishcross facility, in
OL,15,FClackmannanshire, where orphaned and
OL,16,Finjured animals are nursed back to
OL,17,Fhealth.
OL,19,FEmma added: "He was smaller than we'd
OL,20,Fexpect for a newborn, but clearly a
OL,21,Ffighter...he's a little miracle."
